30
00:04:46,699 --> 00:05:06,332
No wonder, then, that, ever gathering volume from the mere transit over the widest watery spaces, the outblown rumours of the white whale did in the end incorporate with themselves all manner of morbid hints and half-formed foetal suggestions of supernatural agencies.

31
00:05:06,312 --> 00:05:12,461
which eventually invested Moby Dick with new terrors unborrowed from anything that visibly appears.

32
00:05:12,701 --> 00:05:26,380
So that in many cases such a panic did he finally strike, that few who, by those rumors at least, had heard of the white whale, few of those hunters were willing to encounter the perils of his jaw.

33
00:05:27,355 --> 00:05:31,803
but there were still other and more vital practical influences at work.

34
00:05:32,003 --> 00:05:45,668
