On this head there are some remarkable documents that may be consulted."

46
00:08:17,158 --> 00:08:24,073
Nevertheless, some there were, who, even in the face of these things, were ready to give chase to Moby Dick.

47
00:08:24,053 --> 00:08:41,370
and a still greater number who, chancing only to hear of him distantly and vaguely, without the specific details of any certain calamity, and without superstitious accompaniments, were sufficiently hardy not to flee from the battle, if offered.

48
00:08:41,350 --> 00:08:56,524
One of the wild suggestions referred to, as at last coming to be linked with the white whale in the minds of the superstitiously inclined, was the unearthly conceit that Moby Dick was ubiquitous.

49
00:08:56,504 --> 00:09:11,003
that he had actually been encountered in opposite latitudes at one and the same instant of time, nor, credulous as such minds must have been, was this conceit altogether without some faint show of superstitious probability.

50
00:09:11,644 --> 00:09:17,913
For us the secrets of the currents in the seas have never yet been divulged, even to the most erudite research.

51
00:09:18,574 --> 00:09:25,583
So the hidden ways of the sperm-whale, when beneath the surface remain, in great part unaccountable to his pursuers.

52
00:09:25,563 --> 00:09:41,412
and from time to time have originated the most curious and contradictory speculations regarding them, especially concerning the mystic modes whereby, after sounding to a great depth, he transports himself with such a vast swiftness to the most widely distant point.

53
00:09:41,392 --> 00:10:01,990
It is a thing well known to both American and English whale-ships, and as well a thing placed upon authoritative record years ago by Scoresby, that some whales have been captured far north in the Pacific, in whose bodies have been found the barbs of harpoons darted in the Greenland seas.

54
00:10:02,210 --> 00:10:11,078
Nor is it to be gainsayed that in some of these instances it has been declared that the interval of time between the two assaults

55
00:10:11,058 --> 00:10:13,643
could not have exceeded very many days.

56
00:10:14,124 --> 00:10:27,953
Hence, by inference, it has been believed by some whalemen that the Norwest Passage, so long a problem to man, was never a problem to the whale, so that here, in the real living experience of living men,

57
00:10:27,933 --> 00:10:49,941
The prodigies related in old times of the inland Strelo Mountain in Portugal, whose start there was said to be a lake in which the wrecks of ships floated up to the surface, and that still more wonderful story of the Arethusa Fountain near Syracuse, whose waters were believed to have come from the Holy Land by an underwrung passage, a dash-dash,

58
00:10:50,427 --> 00:10:54,692
