he would still swim away unharmed under the dark salive indeed he should ever be made to spout thick blog such a sight would but even stripped of these supernatural surmisings there was enough in the earthly make an incontestable character of the monster to strike the imagination with unwanted power

62
00:11:37,373 --> 00:11:51,992
For it was not so much his uncommon bulk that so much distinguished him from other sperm whales, but, as was elsewhere, thrown out a peculiar snow-white wrinkled forehead and a high, pyramidical white hump.

63
00:11:52,012 --> 00:12:03,347
These were his prominent features, the tokens whereby, even in the limitless uncharted seas, he revealed his identity at a long distance to those who knew him.

64
00:12:03,327 --> 00:12:13,779
The rest of his body was so streaked and spotted and marbled with the same shrouded hue that, in the end, he had gained his distinctive appellation of the White Whale.

65
00:12:14,941 --> 00:12:19,466
Ah, a name, indeed, literally justified by his vivid aspect!

66
00:12:20,007 --> 00:12:29,318
When seen gliding, at high noon, through a dark blue sea, leaving a Milky Way wake of creamy foam, all spangled with golden gleamings,

67
00:12:29,467 --> 00:12:49,127
Nor was it his unwanted magnitude, nor his remarkable hue, nor yet his deformed lower jaw, that so much invested the whale with natural terror, as that unexampled intelligent malignity which, according to specific accounts, he had over and over again evinced in his assaults.

68
00:12:49,388 --> 00:12:55,474
More than all, his treacherous retreats struck more of dismay than perhaps aught else.

69
00:12:55,572 --> 00:13:13,716
For, when swimming before his exulting pursuers with every apparent symptom of alarm, he had several times been known to turn round suddenly and, bearing down upon them, either stave their boats to splinters or drive them back in consternation to their ship.

70
00:13:13,747 --> 00:13:17,273
Already several fatalities had attended his chase.

71
00:13:17,453 --> 00:13:23,643
But those similar disasters, however little brooded ashore, were by no means unusual in the fishery.

72
00:13:24,064 --> 00:13:39,248
Yet, in most instances, such seemed the white whale's infernal aforethought of ferocity, that every dismembering, or death that he caused, was not wholly regarded as having been inflicted by an unintelligent agent.

73
00:13:39,228 --> 00:14:02,822
Judged then to what pitches of inflamed, distracted fury the minds of his more desperate hunters were impelled, when amid the chips of chewed boats and the sinking limbs of torn comrades they swam out of the white curds of the whale's direful wrath into the serene, exasperating sunlight that smiled on as if at a birth or a bridal.

74
00:14:02,802 --> 00:14:24,591
His three boats stove around him, and Orison men, both hurling in the eddies one captain, seizing the line-knife from his broken prow, had dashed at the whale, as an Arkansas duelist at his foe, blindly seeking, with a six-inch blade, to reach the fathom-deep life of the whale, that captain was Ahab.

75
00:14:24,571 --> 00:14:35,907
And then it was that, suddenly sweeping his sickle-shaped lower jaw beneath him, Moby Dick had reaped away Ahab's leg as a mower, a blade of grass in the field.

76
00:14:36,728 --> 00:14:42,816
No turbaned Turk, no hired Venetian or Molay, could have smote him with more seeming malice.

77
00:14:42,796 --> 00:15:05,547
Small reason was there to doubt, then, that ever since that almost fatal encounter Ahab had cherished a wild vindictiveness against the whale, all the more fell for that in his frantic morbidness he at last came to identify with him, not only all his bodily woes, but all his intellectual and spiritual exasperations.

78
00:15:05,527 --> 00:15:35,500
The white whale swam before him as the monomaniac incarnation of all those malicious agencies which some deep men feel eating in them, till they are left living on with half a heart and half a lung, that intangible malignity which has been from the beginning, to whose dominion even the modern Christians ascribe one half of the worlds, which the ancient Ophiots of the East, reverence in their statue Devil Ahab, did not fall down.

79
00:15:35,480 --> 00:15:45,425
and worship it like them, but deliriously transferring its idea to the abhorred white whale, he pitted himself, all mutilated, against it.

80
00:15:46,588 --> 00:15:50,839
All that most maddens and torments, all that stirs up the lees of things,

81
00:15:50,819 --> 00:16:06,153
all truth with malice in it, all that cracks the sinews and cakes the brain, all the subtle demonisms of life and thought, all evil, to crazy Ahab were visibly personified and made practically assailable in Moby Dick.

82
00:16:06,753 --> 00:16:14,340
He piled upon the whale's white hump the sum of all the general rage and hate felt by his whole race from Adam down.

83
00:16:15,141 --> 00:16:20,826
And then, as if his chest had been a mortar, he burst his hot heart's shell upon it.

84
00:16:20,806 --> 00:16:28,892
It is not probable that this monomania in him took its instant rise at the precise time of his bodily dismemberment.

85
00:16:29,260 --> 00:16:45,942
Then, in darting at the monster, knife in hand, he had but given loose to a sudden, passionate, corporal animosity, and when he received the stroke that tore him, he probably but felt the agonizing bodily laceration, but nothing more.

86
00:16:46,142 --> 00:16:55,555
Yet, when by this collision forced to turn towards home, and for long months of days and weeks, Ahab and Anguish lay stretched together in one hammock,

87
00:16:55,535 --> 00:16:59,883
rounding in midwinter that dreary-howling Patagonian cape.

88
00:17:00,484 --> 00:17:08,718
Then it was that his torn body and gashed soul bled into one another, and, canned so interfusing, made him mad.

89
00:17:09,239 --> 00:17:13,206
That it was only then, on the homeward voyage, after the encounter,

90
00:17:13,186 --> 00:17:29,271
that the final monomania seized him, seems all but certain from the fact that, at intervals during the passage, he was a raving lunatic, and, though unlimbed of a leg, he had such vital strength yet lurked in his Egyptian chest,

91
00:17:29,251 --> 00:17:38,929
and was moreover intensified by his delirium, that his mates were forced to lace him fasts, even there, as he sailed, raving in his hammock.

92
00:17:39,229 --> 00:17:43,497
In a straight jacket he swung to the mad rockings of the gales.

93
00:17:43,527 --> 00:18:12,690
And when running into more sufferable latitudes, the ship, with mild stun-sail spread, floated across the tranquil tropics, and, to all appearances, the old man's delirium seemed left behind him with the caper and swells, and he came forth from his dark den into the blessed light and air, and even then, when he bore that firm, collected front, however pale, and issued his calm orders once again, and his mates thanked God the direful madness was now gone, even Ahab in his hidden self raved on.

94
00:18:12,670 --> 00:18:17,920
Many a human madness is oftentimes a cunning and most feline thing.

95
00:18:18,601 --> 00:18:24,031
When you think it fled, it may have but become transfigured into some still subtler form.

96
00:18:24,191 --> 00:18:30,443
Ahab's full lunacy subsided not, but deepeningly contracted, like the unabated Hudson.

97
00:18:30,423 --> 00:18:35,913
when that noble Northman flows narrowly, but unfathomably, through the Highland gorge.

98
00:18:36,494 --> 00:18:50,440
But, as in his narrow-flowing monomania, not one jot of Ahab's broad madness had been left behind, so in that broad madness not one jot of his great natural intellect had perished.

99
00:18:50,420 --> 00:18:53,925
that before living agent now became the living instrument.

100
00:18:54,066 --> 00:19:18,503
If such a furious trope may stand, his special lunacy stormed his general sanity, and carried it, and turned all its consented canon upon its own mad marks, so that, far from having lost his strength, Ahab, to that one end, did now possess a thousandfold more potency than ever he had sanely brought to bear upon any one reasonable object,

101
00:19:18,483 --> 00:19:35,496
